Program: Great Lives
Title: Sir Mark Walport on Sir Hans Sloane
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/m000d84w
Last Broadcast Date: Fri 17 Jan 2020
Sir Mark Walport, the government's Chief Scientific Advisor, champions Sir Hans Sloane. Along with expert Marjorie Caygill, he tells Matthew Parris why the British Museum founder is the mother and father of all collectors. Produced by Perminder Khatkar. First broadcast on BBC Radio 4 in April 2014. Show less